                                         CAPE TOWN - No arrests have yet been made in connection with the murder of a police officer in Delft.  The constable was shot last week at his home. The off-duty constable, aged 35, was attacked by two men outside his home in Delft last week. It's believed the South African Police Service member and his pregnant wife had arrived home when they came under attack in their driveway. His spouse rushed him to hospital where he succumbed to his injuries at the weekend.  The motive behind his killing is unclear. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)